node.text:
I’ve been oddly quiet this past week unless you follow @ChrisFished because I have decided I am going on a 400mi trip down to the Chesapeake Bay, up to the Susquehanna River. I’ve spent the last 6 days getting the boat ready (thought it was going to take 2 days lol, what’s new). Part of that is filling up the 170 gallon tank. Boats are a lot different than cars, these engines run at incredibly high RPMs for long periods of time in one of the harshest condition an engine can endure. Think about your car stuck in 3rd gear on the highway with the road being as pothole filled as NYC… To keep her running smooth for the 9hrs of driving each way, I used 3 bottles of @berrymanproducts cetane booster. If a Diesel engine has good fuel, oil, and air, she’s good to go! 

I will be giving updates on @ChrisFished through the whole trip. This is my first time doing this so wish me luck! 

#ChrisFix #BerrymanPartner #ChrisFish #diesel #boat #boating #roadtrip #chesapeakebay #boattrip #fueldock #fishing

I got a lot of questions/comments about the power steering fluid I used because the old cap said “ATF Only”. Since I read the comments of all my videos, I think this is a good one to make a video on! 
The reservoir cap on some BMWs does read “ATF ONLY”. But since 1991 Pentosin started recommending the use of CHF 11S Synthetic Power Steering fluid instead of the CHF 7.1 Power Steering Fluid which used a mineral oil base and is now discontinued.  Pentosin is the OEM supplier of power steering fluid for BMW.
 
While ATF works, the down side is it could eventually cause the seals and hoses to harden and create cracks and leaks in the power steering system.  That’s why I used synthetic power steering fluid instead of ATF.

Code “90AToff” gives you guys $90 off. Link in bio if you want your own scoot scoot! It goes about 15-17mph cruise and the battery lasts about 10miles if you’re flooring it all the time, which you should be or you’re not driving a scooter properly. With a name like TurboAnt you can’t go wrong! These 🐌🐜’s are attention grabbers for sure. I get sooo many looks riding this bad boy. I ride around town with my helmet and people point and take pics. Scoot scoots are also great conversational pieces. And don’t get me started with the ladies... they always ask “can I try?” so you’re going to have to be ready to say NO! I see why @richiebkidd love electric stuff. It’s fun!

node.text:
Finishing up my first ever @chrisfished boat trip which was a lot of fun! Thank you to everyone who gave my new page a follow! It means a lot and they boat and fishing YouTube DIY/How-to videos are coming! 

I’ve been boating since I was in 2nd grade but this trip taught me so much! It also made me realize how we take traveling by car for granted. No waves, the weather doesn’t really matter, you can go 65mph+, you can get more than 2mpg, it takes 2hrs instead of 2 days, and if you break down, you probably won’t die. 

In a few days I’ll be a landlubber again, back in the driveway working on the next video!

I’ve been oddly quiet this past week unless you follow @ChrisFished because I have decided I am going on a 400mi trip down to the Chesapeake Bay, up to the Susquehanna River. I’ve spent the last 6 days getting the boat ready (thought it was going to take 2 days lol, what’s new). Part of that is filling up the 170 gallon tank. Boats are a lot different than cars, these engines run at incredibly high RPMs for long periods of time in one of the harshest condition an engine can endure. Think about your car stuck in 3rd gear on the highway with the road being as pothole filled as NYC… To keep her running smooth for the 9hrs of driving each way, I used 3 bottles of @berrymanproducts cetane booster. If a Diesel engine has good fuel, oil, and air, she’s good to go! 

I will be giving updates on @ChrisFished through the whole trip. This is my first time doing this so wish me luck!
